snippet.title: Death count in ferry sinking tops 100
snippet.description: One by one, coast guard officers carried the newly arrived bodies covered in white sheets from a boat to a tent on the dock of this island, the first step in identifying a sharply rising number of corpses from a South Korean ferry that sank nearly a week ago.

snippet.title: Families' hopes for ferry victims painfully humble
snippet.description: Lee Byung-soo says he knew, when he saw his 15-year-old son's body in the tent. It could not have been more horrifically obvious. But he wanted so much for him to be alive.

snippet.title: US: Russia has 'days, not weeks' to follow accord
snippet.description: Russia has "days, not weeks" to abide by an international accord aimed at stemming the crisis in Ukraine, the top U.S. diplomat in Kiev warned Monday as Vice President Joe Biden launched a high-profile show of support for the pro-Western Ukrainian government. Russia in turn accused authorities in Kiev of flagrantly violating the pact and declared their actions would not stand.

snippet.title: Might crafts such as knitting offer long-term health benefits?
snippet.description: It's not just about the pretty scarf. Research shows the benefits of the hobby on long-term health.

snippet.title: Biden in Ukraine to show support as tensions rise
snippet.description: Vice President Joe Biden on Monday launched a high-profile visit to demonstrate the U.S. commitment to Ukraine and push for urgent implementation of an international agreement aimed at de-escalating tensions even as violence continues. The United States will decide within "days, not weeks" whether Russia is abiding by the accord, a U.S. diplomat said.

snippet.title: AT&T explores expansion of super-fast Internet
snippet.description: AT&T plans a major expansion of super-fast Internet services to cover as many as 100 municipalities in 25 metropolitan areas.

snippet.title: Mary Cheney launches polling firm
snippet.description: Republican consultant and former aide to George W. Bush's campaigns teams up with other GOP activists to launch new firm.

snippet.title: Are we fact-checking pop culture to death?
snippet.description: Critics are pushing back against attempts to fact-check pop culture. So when does it matter when pop culture gets things wrong?

snippet.title: Loudoun County community calendar, April 20-27, 2014
snippet.description: Events include a flower and garden festival, bluegrass music, a horse show and a hymn sing.

snippet.title: 2014 draft: Kouandjio and the top 10 tackles
snippet.description: The Redskins aim to upgrade the offensive line in the draft. Cyrus Kouandjio, a tackle from DeMatha High and Alabama, is among Mike Jones's best available.
